{
  "texts": [
    "In the search process, it was necessary to resort to specific keywords to locate all the cases, without limiting the search to the mandatory appearance of those keywords.",
    "Many of the papers with different purposes shared keywords, such as \"VR\" in articles that reported the use or made no mention of HMDs, or \"reconstruction\" in 3D reconstruction and photogrammetry papers.",
    "Finally, some papers that appeared in the bibliography of the sample were added to the review, in an example of a snowball effect.Figure 2 depicts the steps of the process following the PRISMA methodology, which left a total of 94 papers [16,.The title and the abstract of each paper were read to select the ones to be included and to verify whether they fitted the requirements of the analysis.",
    "If the information was not clearly explained in the abstract, a first reading was performed to determine whether to include the paper in the review.",
    "Once selected, the papers were analysed on a spreadsheet that was also used for the statistical analyses."
  ]
}